# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project-specific: internal docs and planning (not for public GitHub)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exclude docs/ by default, but re-include the two extension references
# that are genuinely useful for readers on GitHub.
docs/*
!docs/adapter_pattern.md
!docs/pillar3_pdf_spec.md
!docs/migration_from_adjusted_to_raw.md
!docs/INDUSTRY_ANALYSIS_INTEGRATION_SPEC.md
PROGRESS.md

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project-specific: raw data and local DB
# (too large and/or source-owned; reproducible via scripts/download_sources
# and `python cli.py ingest ...`)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
data/
benchmarks.db

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Project-specific: generated outputs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default: outputs/ not tracked. Exception: the Brief 1 raw-only sample
# report is committed so GitHub visitors can see example output without
# having to run the pipeline themselves. Future cycles add their
# period-specific whitelist entries.
outputs/*
!outputs/reports/
outputs/reports/*
!outputs/reports/Report_Q1_2026_RawOnly_sample.md
# Environment reports (sibling industry-analysis project) — kept when present.
!outputs/reports/Report_Environment_*.md
!outputs/reports/Report_Environment_*.html
!outputs/reports/Report_Environment_*.docx
